data.enText: to give a document, proposal, etc. to sb in authority so that they can study or consider it

data.chText: 呈递申请书 / 书面要求；提交控诉书
data.enText: to submit an application/a claim/a complaint

data.chText: 完成的方案必须在3月10日前提交上来。
data.enText: Completed projects must be submitted by 10 March.

data.chText: 顺从；屈服；投降；不得已接受
data.enText: to accept the authority, control or greater strength of sb/sth; to agree to sth because of this
She refused to submit to threats.
He submitted himself to a search by the guards.

data.chText: 被告律师认为这一证据不可采纳。
data.enText: Counsel for the defence submitted that the evidence was inadmissible.

simple_means.memory_skill: sub 下 + mit 送，放出 → 放下 → 屈服

ex.chText: 他把作文交给了老师。
ex.enText: He handed his composition to the teacher.

ex.chText: 这张表格必须交给所有员工。
ex.enText: This form must be handed to all the staff members.

synonyms.bx: 指将某物亲手交给他人。

ex.chText: 请把报纸递给我。
ex.enText: Pass me the paper, please.

ex.chText: 她把一杯咖啡递给经理。
ex.enText: She passed a cup of coffee to the manager.

ex.chText: 把球传给他。
ex.enText: Pass him the ball.

synonyms.bx: 指把某人可以看到但够不到的东西给某人。

ex.chText: 向委员会提交了大约40篇论文。
ex.enText: Some 40 papers were presented to the committee.

ex.chText: 大使向总统递交了国书。
ex.enText: The ambassador presented his credentials to the president.

synonyms.bx: 指将某物呈递给某人、某一机构等，通常用于正式场合。

ex.chText: 草案已经呈递给总统。
ex.enText: The draft was submitted to the president.

ex.chText: 我们应该向理事会提交计划以求批准。
ex.enText: We should submit our plan to the council for approval.

ex.chText: 我们还是把争执提交仲裁吧。
ex.enText: Let's submit our disputes for arbitration.

synonyms.bx: 指把计划等呈交给上级或权威人士审批或审查。

ex.chText: 士兵们发誓宁死不降。
ex.enText: The soldiers vowed that they would rather die than surrender.

ex.chText: 我们决不会向邪恶势力低头。
ex.enText: We will never surrender to evil.

ex.chText: 在这种压力下，你能不屈服吗?
ex.enText: Couldn't you surrender under such pressure?

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指因战败而投降，或指在压力下屈服让步，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 叛乱者被迫投降。
ex.enText: The rebels were forced to give in.

ex.chText: 他最后向妻子作出了让步。
ex.enText: Finally, he gave in to his wife.

ex.chText: 只有懦夫才向命运屈服。
ex.enText: Only a coward gives in to his fate.

synonyms.bx: 用法不如 surrender 正式，可后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 他们没有向敌人屈服。
ex.enText: They did not submit to the enemy.

ex.chText: 矿工们面对威胁，拒不低头。
ex.enText: The miners refused to submit to threats.

ex.chText: 你怎么能甘受这种虐待呢?
ex.enText: How could you submit to such ill treatment?

synonyms.bx: 通常指放弃抵抗，屈服于某一势力、权力、意志等。

ex.chText: 我们决不会向侵略者屈服。
ex.enText: We will never yield to invaders.

ex.chText: 他没有向对手屈服。
ex.enText: He didn't yield himself to his rival.

ex.chText: 我尊重法律，不会屈服于任何压力。
ex.enText: I won't yield to any pressure in my respect for the law.

synonyms.bx: 通常指放弃抵抗而投降，也可指因缺乏坚强的意志、忍耐力等而屈从于某种权势或压力，常后接介词 to。

example: He resigned himself to his fate
I submit to you that the accused is guilty

tr: yield to another's wish or opinion
example: The government bowed to the military pressure
The lawyers submitted the material to the court

tr: make an application as for a job or funding
example: We put in a grant to the NSF

tr: yield to the control of another

example: They had to render the estate

tr: refer to another person for decision or judgment
example: She likes to relegate difficult questions to her colleagues

value.def: If you submit to something, you unwillingly allow something to be done to you, or you do what someone wants, for example because you are not powerful enough to resist.

example.ex: In desperation, Mrs. Jones submitted to an operation on her right knee to relieve the pain...
example.tran: 绝望之际，琼斯夫人只好同意在其右膝上做手术以减轻疼痛。

example.ex: If I submitted to their demands, they would not press the allegations.
example.tran: 如果那时我答应他们的要求，他们就不会坚持那些指控了。

value.tran: 顺从;屈服;投降;被迫接受

value.def: If you submit a proposal, report, or request to someone, you formally send it to them so that they can consider it or decide about it.

example.ex: They submitted their reports to the Chancellor yesterday...
example.tran: 他们昨天向财政大臣递交了报告。

example.ex: Head teachers yesterday submitted a claim for a 9 per cent pay rise.
example.tran: 校长们昨天提交了一份要求加薪 9%的声明。

value.tran: 提交，递呈(建议、报告或请求)

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to send, to cast 送, 放出
rootsaffixes.title: miss, mit

partsOfSpeech.dec: ad 加强 + mit 送，放出 → 送来 → 准许…进入
com 共同 + miss 送，放出 + ion 表名词 → 共同送出〔选出〕的人 → 委员会
com 共同 + mit 送，放出 → 共同派送 → 委任
dis 加强 + miss 送，放出 → 不断把人送出 → 解散
e 出 + miss 送，放出 + ary 表人 → 派出去的人 → 使者
e 出 + mit 送，放出 → 放出〔气味、光亮〕等 → 发光；发出〔气味等〕
e 出 + miss 送，放出 + ion 表名词 → 发出，放射
e 出 + miss 送，放出 + ive …的 → 发出的，放射的
inter 在…之间 + mit 送，放出 → 在发送之间〔间断〕→ 暂停，间断
intermit的形容词
miss 送，放出 + ion 表名词 → 送出 → 派遣
mission 派遣；使命 + ary 表人 →〔肩负传教〕使命 → 教士
per 自始至终 + mit 送，放出 → 始终〔允许〕发送 → 许可
permit的名词
permit的形容词
re 一再 + miss 送，放出 → 一再放走，错过的 → 粗心的
re 一再 + mit 送，放出 →〔把钱〕再送出去 → 汇款
sub 下 + mit 送，放出 → 放下 → 屈服
submit的名词
trans 横过 + mit 送，放出 → 跨距离传达、寄送 → 传达
trans 横过，越过 + miss 送，放出 + ion 表名词 → 跨距离转送、传达 → 转送；传达
